The All Progressives Congress’ national secretariat will on Monday (today) unveil the modalities for the sharing of party positions between the Kano State Governor, Abdullahi Ganduje-led faction of the party in the state and that of Senator Ibrahim Shekarau’s faction. Shekarau’s spokesman, Dr Sule Sule, confirmed the development to our correspondent on Sunday. Sule said the development was the outcome of a meeting held  Saturday night betweenthe two camps. According to him, the meeting was initiated by the APC Caretaker and Extraordinary National Convention Planning Committee, led by its Chairman, Mai Mala Buni, with Zamfara State Governor, Bello Matawalle, and former Speaker of the House of Representatives, Yakubu Dogara, in attendance. “We made our own position and they made theirs and now they have deliberated on the two positions and resolved that they are coming up with a sharing formula, which they said will be all-inclusive, meaning that all of us will be part of the executives. “A high-powered committee from the secretariat is to be constituted and deployed to Kano to ensure strict compliance and implementation of the template to be given on Monday (today),” Sule said.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com